subSubSection.paragraph:
Pereopods
(
Figs. 7–8
) Pereopods 3 and 4 subequal, 6-articulate, coxae large (
Fig. 9
); carpus with 3 grasping spines; propodus with 2 proximal grasping spines, row of setae ventrally and thick bunch of setae dorsodistally. Pereopod 5 6-articulate; carpus with grasping spine; propodus without grasping spine, with thick bunch of setae dorsodistally; dactylus short, curved. Pereopods 6 and 7 subequal, 6-articulate; merus with grasping spine; carpus with 3 grasping spines; propodus with 2 pairs of grasping spines proximally and smaller spine distally; dactylus with setules.
